{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nBring the symmetric HMAC signer (`src/rebar/signing.py`, algorithm id `HMAC-SHA256`) into the new attest scheme registry (`src/rebar/attest/registry.py`, task 518b) as a **legacy scheme**, so the substrate acknowledges HMAC and both consumer epics can reference one registry. This is the **expand** phase: existing plan-review / completion-verifier attestations must keep verifying **unchanged** through the untouched `signing.py` path (the HMAC->asymmetric cutover is the op-cert epic contract phase, out of scope here).\n\n## Dispatch contract (concrete)\n- A **legacy record** is a stored attestation whose `algorithm` field is `HMAC-SHA256`, **or absent** (absent defaults to `HMAC-SHA256` ŌĆö matches `signing.verify_record`, which always applies HMAC-SHA256 and ignores any stored algorithm).\n- The registry `Scheme` is selected by `POLICY[kind].scheme`; the HMAC scheme is keyed by its algorithm id `signing.ALGORITHM` (`\"HMAC-SHA256\"`).\n- `HmacScheme.verify(pae_bytes, signatures, namespace, trust_root)` computes HMAC-SHA256 over `pae_bytes` with the key supplied as `trust_root` and constant-time-compares (`hmac.compare_digest`) to `signatures[0].sig`; an empty/missing key fails **closed** (`Verdict(verified=False, verdict=\"foreign_key\")`), a non-matching sig -> `verdict=\"mismatch\"`, a match -> `verdict=\"certified\"`.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/attest/hmac_legacy.py` ŌĆö `HmacScheme` (implements the registry `Scheme` protocol) + `register_legacy_schemes()` bootstrap that registers it and pins `POLICY` entries for the legacy kinds `plan-review` and `completion-verifier` to `Policy(scheme=\"HMAC-SHA256\", namespace=\"rebar-attest-hmac\")`.\n- `src/rebar/attest/__init__.py` ŌĆö call `register_legacy_schemes()` at import so the built-in scheme is always available.\n- `src/rebar/signing.py` ŌĆö **unchanged** (regression guard: no edits to sign/verify functions).\n- `tests/unit/test_attest_hmac_legacy.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `HmacScheme` is registered in the registry keyed by algorithm id `HMAC-SHA256` (`registry.get_scheme(\"HMAC-SHA256\")` returns it) and `registry.resolve(\"plan-review\").scheme == \"HMAC-SHA256\"` (and likewise `completion-verifier`); a test asserts both.\n- [ ] `HmacScheme.verify` over DSSE-PAE bytes returns `certified` with the correct key as `trust_root`, and fails **closed** (`mismatch` on wrong key, `foreign_key` on empty key) ŌĆö test matrix.\n- [ ] Regression: a plan-review/completion-verifier attestation created via `signing.sign_manifest` still returns `verdict == \"certified\"` from `signing.verify_signature` (existing path unchanged) ŌĆö regression test.\n- [ ] No behavior change to existing `signing.py` sign/verify paths (the module diff is limited to registration wiring elsewhere; a test signs+verifies a manifest exactly as before and gets `certified`)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783786753521124001,"uuid":"e923e0f5-9736-41fd-9043-66858bd631d3"}